---
title: "FIG. 12 — Cross-Phase Escalation Protocol"
---
sequenceDiagram
    participant H as 1200 — Human
    participant DA as 1210 — Design Agent<br/>(Downstream)
    participant P as 1220 — Platform<br/>Escalation Manager
    participant PA as 1230 — PM Agent<br/>(Upstream)
    participant VC as 1240 — Version Control

    H->>DA: 1201 — Design conversation

    Note over DA: 1202 — Detects blocking question:<br/>[type: product] [blocking: yes]<br/>"What auth provider to use?"

    DA->>H: 1203 — "This is a product decision.<br/>Shall I bring in the PM?"

    H->>P: 1204 — "Yes"

    Note over P: 1205 — Construct upstream<br/>agent payload

    P->>VC: 1206 — Load current draft excerpt
    VC-->>P: Draft content

    P->>PA: 1207 — Invoke PM with:<br/>- Blocking question<br/>- Draft excerpt<br/>- Conversation history

    Note over PA: 1208 — Opens with concrete<br/>answer proposal<br/>(not discovery questions)

    PA-->>H: 1209 — "My recommendation:<br/>Use OAuth 2.0 with Google<br/>because [rationale]..."

    H->>PA: 1210 — Confirms or iterates

    PA-->>P: 1211 — Resolution confirmed

    Note over P: 1212 — Clear escalation state.<br/>Inject PM decision into<br/>design agent context.

    P->>DA: 1213 — Resume design agent<br/>with injected decision

    DA-->>H: 1214 — Continues design spec<br/>with PM answer incorporated
